were not in
favor of building this machine.

47:14.965 --> 47:18.803 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: In telling the
story of the
human drama, inevitably, you get
into jealousies,

47:18.836 --> 47:24.675 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
you get into failures, you get
into all kinds
of human dramas.

47:24.709 --> 47:25.843 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JANNA LEVIN: Yes. Yes.

47:25.876 --> 47:27.845 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: But that is part
of the story.

47:27.878 --> 47:30.881 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JANNA LEVIN: Well, I think what
people don't
appreciate is, that's really how
science is

47:30.915 --> 47:32.750 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
done.

47:32.783 --> 47:35.352 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
People think that we just come
down with these
answers. As scientists, we are
full of answers.

47:35.386 --> 47:38.923 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
That's really not what it is
like. Scientists
are full of questions.
Sometimes, the questions

47:38.956 --> 47:42.793 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
don't lead you to the answer,
