people made it to the summit,
and some people

47:50.868 --> 47:52.570 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
didn't.

47:52.603 --> 47:54.605 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Tell me about
your own way
into this. You write. You study
this. You

47:54.638 --> 47:55.506 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
write about black holes.

47:55.539 --> 47:56.707 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JANNA LEVIN: Yes.

47:56.741 --> 47:58.008 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I have spent a lot of time
thinking about
black holes.

47:58.042 --> 47:59.643 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JEFFREY BROWN: Yes.

47:59.677 --> 48:01.412 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
JANNA LEVIN: And I'm a
theoretical astrophysicist.
So I work on pen and paper.

48:01.445 --> 48:06.050 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It is very abstract. It is kind
