were hundreds

50:30.828 --> 50:35.566 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
of billions of stars in
collections called
galaxies, or that there were
quasars powered

50:35.599 --> 50:37.368 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
by black holes.

50:37.401 --> 50:41.906 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
These were things you couldn't
foresee. And
I think what Kip hopes and what
a lot of us

50:41.939 --> 50:48.812 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
hope is that the future will be
so vast, beyond
what we have even imagined, that
there are

50:48.846 --> 50:53.617 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
